Description: Fragment of sub-round handle from neck join to sharp turn of a Rhodian pottery transport amphora. Clay fine light brown. Rectangular stamp.
Curator's comments: Ink, deleted, '2̣61'. Name Timagoras. From same die as Alexandria, Greco-Roman Museum, ABC 0219.40?
Bibliographic references: Stoddart 1847 / Memoir on the inscribed pottery of Rhodes, Cnidus and other Greek Cities (260)
